22namespace webrtc {
23namespace {
24// If no calls to MaybeProcessPackets() happen, make sure we update stats
25// at least every |kMaxTimeBetweenStatsUpdates| as long as the pacer isn't
26// completely drained.
27constexpr TimeDelta kMaxTimeBetweenStatsUpdates = TimeDelta::Millis(33);
28// Don't call UpdateStats() more than |kMinTimeBetweenStatsUpdates| apart,
29// for performance reasons.
30constexpr TimeDelta kMinTimeBetweenStatsUpdates = TimeDelta::Millis(1);
31} // namespace
32
33TaskQueuePacedSender::TaskQueuePacedSender(
34 Clock* clock,
35 PacingController::PacketSender* packet_sender,
36 RtcEventLog* event_log,
37 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* field_trials,
38 TaskQueueFactory* task_queue_factory,
39 TimeDelta hold_back_window)
40 : clock_(clock),
41 hold_back_window_(hold_back_window),
42 pacing_controller_(clock,
43 packet_sender,
44 event_log,
45 field_trials,
46 PacingController::ProcessMode::kDynamic),
47 next_process_time_(Timestamp::MinusInfinity()),
48 stats_update_scheduled_(false),
49 last_stats_time_(Timestamp::MinusInfinity()),
50 is_shutdown_(false),
51 task_queue_(task_queue_factory->CreateTaskQueue(
52 "TaskQueuePacedSender",
53 TaskQueueFactory::Priority::NORMAL)) {}
54
55TaskQueuePacedSender::~TaskQueuePacedSender() {
56 // Post an immediate task to mark the queue as shutting down.
57 // The rtc::TaskQueue destructor will wait for pending tasks to
58 // complete before continuing.
59 task_queue_.PostTask([&]() {
60 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
61 is_shutdown_ = true;
62 });
63}
64
65void TaskQueuePacedSender::EnsureStarted() {
66 task_queue_.PostTask([this]() {
67 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
68 is_started_ = true;
69 MaybeProcessPackets(Timestamp::MinusInfinity());
70 });
71}

73void TaskQueuePacedSender::CreateProbeCluster(DataRate bitrate,
74 int cluster_id) {
75 task_queue_.PostTask([this, bitrate, cluster_id]() {
76 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
77 pacing_controller_.CreateProbeCluster(bitrate, cluster_id);
78 MaybeProcessPackets(Timestamp::MinusInfinity());
79 });
80}

105
106void TaskQueuePacedSender::UpdateOutstandingData(DataSize outstanding_data) {
107 if (task_queue_.IsCurrent()) {
108 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
109 // Fast path since this can be called once per sent packet while on the
110 // task queue.
111 pacing_controller_.UpdateOutstandingData(outstanding_data);
112 return;
113 }
114
115 task_queue_.PostTask([this, outstanding_data]() {
116 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
117 pacing_controller_.UpdateOutstandingData(outstanding_data);
118 MaybeProcessPackets(Timestamp::MinusInfinity());
119 });
120}
121
122void TaskQueuePacedSender::SetPacingRates(DataRate pacing_rate,
123 DataRate padding_rate) {
124 task_queue_.PostTask([this, pacing_rate, padding_rate]() {
125 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
126 pacing_controller_.SetPacingRates(pacing_rate, padding_rate);
127 MaybeProcessPackets(Timestamp::MinusInfinity());
128 });
129}
130
131void TaskQueuePacedSender::EnqueuePackets(
132 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> packets) {
133#if RTC_TRACE_EVENTS_ENABLED
134 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("webrtc"),
135 "TaskQueuePacedSender::EnqueuePackets");
136 for (auto& packet : packets) {
137 TRACE_EVENT2(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("webrtc"),
138 "TaskQueuePacedSender::EnqueuePackets::Loop",
139 "sequence_number", packet->SequenceNumber(), "rtp_timestamp",
140 packet->Timestamp());
141 }
142#endif
143
144 task_queue_.PostTask([this, packets_ = std::move(packets)]() mutable {
145 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
146 for (auto& packet : packets_) {
147 RTC_DCHECK_GE(packet->capture_time_ms(), 0);
148 pacing_controller_.EnqueuePacket(std::move(packet));
149 }
150 MaybeProcessPackets(Timestamp::MinusInfinity());
151 });
152}

199void TaskQueuePacedSender::OnStatsUpdated(const Stats& stats) {
200 MutexLock lock(&stats_mutex_);
201 current_stats_ = stats;
202}
203
204void TaskQueuePacedSender::MaybeProcessPackets(
205 Timestamp scheduled_process_time) {
206 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
207
208 if (is_shutdown_ || !is_started_) {
209 return;
210 }
211
212 // Normally, run ProcessPackets() only if this is the scheduled task.
213 // If it is not but it is already time to process and there either is
214 // no scheduled task or the schedule has shifted forward in time, run
215 // anyway and clear any schedule.
216 Timestamp next_process_time = pacing_controller_.NextSendTime();
217 const Timestamp now = clock_->CurrentTime();
218 const bool is_scheduled_call = next_process_time_ == scheduled_process_time;
219 if (is_scheduled_call) {
220 // Indicate no pending scheduled call.
221 next_process_time_ = Timestamp::MinusInfinity();
222 }
223 if (is_scheduled_call ||
224 (now >= next_process_time && (next_process_time_.IsInfinite() ||
225 next_process_time < next_process_time_))) {
226 pacing_controller_.ProcessPackets();
227 next_process_time = pacing_controller_.NextSendTime();
228 }
229
230 absl::optional<TimeDelta> time_to_next_process;
231 if (pacing_controller_.IsProbing() &&
232 next_process_time != next_process_time_) {
233 // If we're probing and there isn't already a wakeup scheduled for the next
234 // process time, always post a task and just round sleep time down to
235 // nearest millisecond.
236 if (next_process_time.IsMinusInfinity()) {
237 time_to_next_process = TimeDelta::Zero();
238 } else {
239 time_to_next_process =
240 std::max(TimeDelta::Zero(),
241 (next_process_time - now).RoundDownTo(TimeDelta::Millis(1)));
242 }
243 } else if (next_process_time_.IsMinusInfinity() ||
244 next_process_time <= next_process_time_ - hold_back_window_) {
245 // Schedule a new task since there is none currently scheduled
246 // (|next_process_time_| is infinite), or the new process time is at least
247 // one holdback window earlier than whatever is currently scheduled.
248 time_to_next_process = std::max(next_process_time - now, hold_back_window_);
249 }
250
251 if (time_to_next_process) {
252 // Set a new scheduled process time and post a delayed task.
253 next_process_time_ = next_process_time;
254
255 task_queue_.PostDelayedTask(
256 [this, next_process_time]() { MaybeProcessPackets(next_process_time); },
257 time_to_next_process->ms<uint32_t>());
258 }
259
260 MaybeUpdateStats(false);
261}
262
263void TaskQueuePacedSender::MaybeUpdateStats(bool is_scheduled_call) {
264 if (is_shutdown_) {
265 if (is_scheduled_call) {
266 stats_update_scheduled_ = false;
267 }
268 return;
269 }
270
271 Timestamp now = clock_->CurrentTime();
272 if (is_scheduled_call) {
273 // Allow scheduled task to process packets to clear up an remaining debt
274 // level in an otherwise empty queue.
275 pacing_controller_.ProcessPackets();
276 } else {
277 if (now - last_stats_time_ < kMinTimeBetweenStatsUpdates) {
278 // Too frequent unscheduled stats update, return early.
279 return;
280 }
281 }
282
283 Stats new_stats;
284 new_stats.expected_queue_time = pacing_controller_.ExpectedQueueTime();
285 new_stats.first_sent_packet_time = pacing_controller_.FirstSentPacketTime();
286 new_stats.oldest_packet_wait_time = pacing_controller_.OldestPacketWaitTime();
287 new_stats.queue_size = pacing_controller_.QueueSizeData();
288 OnStatsUpdated(new_stats);
289
290 last_stats_time_ = now;
291
292 bool pacer_drained = pacing_controller_.QueueSizePackets() == 0 &&
293 pacing_controller_.CurrentBufferLevel().IsZero();
294
295 // If there's anything interesting to get from the pacer and this is a
296 // scheduled call (or no scheduled call in flight), post a new scheduled stats
297 // update.
298 if (!pacer_drained) {
299 if (!stats_update_scheduled_) {
300 // There is no pending delayed task to update stats, add one.
301 // Treat this call as being scheduled in order to bootstrap scheduling
302 // loop.
303 stats_update_scheduled_ = true;
304 is_scheduled_call = true;
305 }
306
307 // Only if on the scheduled call loop do we want to schedule a new delayed
308 // task.
309 if (is_scheduled_call) {
310 task_queue_.PostDelayedTask(
311 [this]() {
312 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
313 MaybeUpdateStats(true);
314 },
315 kMaxTimeBetweenStatsUpdates.ms<uint32_t>());
316 }
317 } else if (is_scheduled_call) {
318 // This is a scheduled call, signing out since there's nothing interesting
319 // left to check.
320 stats_update_scheduled_ = false;
321 }
322}
323
324TaskQueuePacedSender::Stats TaskQueuePacedSender::GetStats() const {
325 MutexLock lock(&stats_mutex_);
326 return current_stats_;
327}
